{"type":"item.completed","item":{"id":"item_8","type":"command_execution","command":"/bin/bash -lc \"sed -n '1,260p' /home/daytona/workspace/apps/waketask-ios/README.md\"","aggregated_output":"# WakeTask\n\nWakeTask is an iPhone alarm accountability app. Instead of letting a user dismiss an alarm passively, it guides them through a wake run: dismiss the alarm, complete a wake check, finish a first task, and build a reliability history.\n\nThe app is built on SwiftAIBoilerplatePro modules for authentication, payments, storage, networking, localization, settings, and design system. WakeTask-specific product code lives in the `Wake` app shell, localization keys, storage models, tests, and exploratory UI flow.\n\n## Current Release Target\n\n- App name: `WakeTask`\n- Bundle id: `com.keen.waketask`\n- iOS target: iOS 17+\n- Toolchain target: Xcode 26.2+ on macOS 15+\n- Signing team in project: `LL4Y637Z4Y`\n- Version: `1.0` build `1`\n\n## Product Surface\n\n- Wake dashboard with alarm contracts and weekly consistency.\n- Alarm creation flow with strictness and first-task commitment.\n- Active wake run with mission progression before final dismissal.\n- Local wake run persistence using the Storage package.\n- Accessibility labels for alarm creation, mission completion, and dismissal controls.\n- English and Spanish localization keys for the Wake surface.\n\n## Repository Layout\n\n```text\nSwiftAIBoilerplatePro.xcodeproj/   Xcode project\nSwiftAIBoilerplatePro/             App target and Wake UI\nPackages/                         Shared packages reused from SwiftAIBoilerplatePro\nSwiftAIBoilerplateProTests/        Unit tests, including WakeTask tests\nSwiftAIBoilerplateProUITests/      XCUITest exploratory wake run\nConfig/                           App and local secret config templates\nscripts/ci/                       Hosted macOS quality gates\nscripts/qa/                       Exploratory XCUITest/Appium-style report script\nsupabase/                         Optional AI proxy backend\n```\n\n## Local Setup\n\nThis machine needs full Xcode, not only Command Line Tools.\n\n```bash\nopen SwiftAIBoilerplatePro.xcodeproj\n```\n\nAfter Xcode installs, run:\n\n```bash\n./scripts/local/doctor.sh\n./scripts/local/run-simulator.sh build\n```\n\nSee `LOCAL_TESTING.md` for simulator, physical iPhone, and TestFlight preparation steps.\n\nThe app can run in debug with mock auth and placeholder service config. Production service values should be placed in `Config/Secrets.xcconfig`, which is gitignored.\n\n```bash\ncp Config/Secrets.example.xcconfig Config/Secrets.xcconfig\nbash scripts/update-config.sh\n```\n\nDo not commit `Config/Secrets.xcconfig` or generated real credentials.\n\n## Hosted CI\n\nThe main gate is `.github/workflows/ios-quality.yml`.\n\nIt runs on GitHub-hosted macOS and checks:\n\n- `xcodebuild` package resolution, build, and tests\n- SwiftLint\n- SwiftFormat\n- Qlty\n- sensitive-value scanning\n- Release binary App Store 4.3 string audit\n- WakeTask exploratory UI traversal\n- uploaded `reports/ios/ios-quality-report.json`\n- uploaded `reports/ios/appium-exploratory-report.json`\n\nManual dispatch:\n\n```bash\ngh workflow run \"iOS Quality\" --ref main\n```\n\nWatch:\n\n```bash\ngh run list --workflow ios-quality.yml --limit 5\ngh run watch <run-id>\n```\n\n## App Store Readiness\n\nBefore TestFlight/App Store submission:\n\n- Confirm the Apple Developer account owns bundle id `com.keen.waketask`.\n- Confirm signing team `LL4Y637Z4Y` is correct for the target account.\n- Set production Supabase, RevenueCat, AI proxy, and optional OneSignal values.\n- Use the RevenueCat Test Store key only for Debug/local testing; TestFlight/App Store builds require the iOS app-specific RevenueCat key.\n- Run the hosted `iOS Quality` workflow on `main`.\n- Confirm both uploaded reports are present and passing.\n- Archive in Xcode or wire a signing-enabled GitHub Actions archive job.\n- Create the App Store Connect app record, privacy answers, screenshots, description, keywords, support URL, and review notes.\n\nActual App Store submission should happen only after a successful TestFlight/internal QA pass.\n","exit_code":0,"status":"completed"}}
